Show HN: Chrome Extension – Navigate to Founders LinkedIn Page from CrunchBase
text:
A Chrome Extension that allows you to navigate to people's LinkedIn page from CrunchBase with one-click without premium subscription.

I use Crunchbase a lot. I use it mostly to query the funding and founders information of startup companies. The feature that allows one-click to founders' LinkedIn page is only available for premium subscription, I don't use it enough to justify paying for it. So I have to copy founders name and search it on LinkedIn manually. This becomes a pain over the time. So I decided to create a Chrome extension so that I can navigate to founders LinkedIn page with a single click.

Get started: 1. Install it from Chrome Web Store 2. Open Crunchbase and find the company you want to query and go to the "People" page of the company. Make sure the "Contacts" section is not empty 4. Open Crunchbase People Chrome extension from the top right corner of Chrome. The popup window lists the people and their titles that are available from the Crunchbase's page 5. Click them and it will open a new tab which leads to their LinkedIn page.

I hope you like it. The source code is on github: https://github.com/narisong/crunchbase

Ask HN: How to cancel Adobe CC subscription without paying a “cancellation fee”?
text:
I want to cancel my Adobe CC subscription. I don't use the software anywhere near often enough to justify the cost of it.

When trying to cancel my subscription I was faced with a ridiculous "cancellation fee." Surely this can't be legal? How do I avoid paying this outrageous money grab?

It goes without saying that I'm never going to use any of their products again.
